You are working inside the Mixa AI PRD workspace.

This workspace contains the Product Requirements Document (PRD) for Mixa AI.

## Context
- The PRD is the single source of truth for product requirements.
- It lives inside a Turborepo monorepo at `docs/prd/`.
- The monorepo will eventually contain apps in `apps/` and shared packages in `packages/`.

## Guidelines
- When editing the PRD, preserve the existing section structure.
- Use clear, concise language. Avoid jargon unless it's defined.
- Every requirement should be testable or verifiable.
- Flag open questions in the "Open Questions" section rather than leaving ambiguity inline.
- When adding user stories, follow the format: "As a [persona], I want [action] so that [outcome]."
